---
import SidebarLayout from '../../layouts/SidebarLayout.astro';

const stripeUrl = import.meta.env.PUBLIC_STRIPE_BUY_URL;

const images = {
  hero: '/cases/images/hero-loch-ness-panorama.jpg',
  surgeons: '/cases/images/evidence-surgeons-photograph-1934.jpg',
  urquhartRuins: '/cases/images/atmosphere-urquhart-castle-ruins.jpg',
  plesiosaur: '/cases/images/atmosphere-duria-antiquior-plesiosaur-1830.jpg',
  columba: '/cases/images/figure-saint-columba.jpg',
  kelpie: '/cases/images/atmosphere-kelpie-water-horse.jpg',
  highlands: '/cases/images/atmosphere-loch-ness-highlands.jpg',
};
---

<SidebarLayout title="The Loch Ness Monster" description="The Hunt for Scotland's Impossible Creature" currentVolume={8}>
  <article class="case-file">

    <!-- HERO SECTION -->
    <header class="hero">
      <div class="hero-bg">
        <img src={images.hero} alt="" />
        <div class="hero-overlay"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="hero-content">
        <div class="case-meta">
          <span class="meta-badge price">$2.99</span>
          <span class="meta-badge">CASE 02-1933</span>
          <span class="meta-badge alert">STATUS: LIKELY MYTH</span>
        </div>

        <h1 class="hero-title">The Loch Ness Monster</h1>
        <p class="hero-subtitle">The Hunt for Scotland's Impossible Creature</p>

        <div class="hero-stats">
          <div class="stat">
            <span class="stat-label">First Sighting</span>
            <span class="stat-value">565 AD</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stat">
            <span class="stat-label">Photo Exposed</span>
            <span class="stat-value">1994</span>
          </div>
           <div class="stat">
            <span class="stat-label">Confidence</span>
            <span class="stat-value text-accent">85%</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="hero-actions">
          <button onclick={`localStorage.setItem('historiqly_purchasing','loch-ness-monster');window.location.href='${stripeUrl}'`} class="btn-buy-primary" id="heroBuyBtn">
            <span class="btn-buy-text">Buy the Book</span>
            <span class="btn-buy-price">$2.99</span>
          </button>
          <a href="/books/epub/loch-ness-monster.epub" class="btn-download-primary" id="heroDownloadBtn" style="display:none;" download>
            <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5">
              <path d="M21 15v4a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2v-4"></path>
              <polyline points="7 10 12 15 17 10"></polyline>
              <line x1="12" y1="15" x2="12" y2="3"></line>
            </svg>
            <span>Download Your Book</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

       <div class="scroll-indicator">
        <span>INVESTIGATE</span>
        <div class="scroll-line"></div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <!-- THE HOOK -->
    <section class="intro-section">
      <div class="intro-text">
        <p class="drop-cap">In April 1934, a London surgeon photographed a long-necked creature rising from the dark waters of a Scottish loch. The image became the most famous photograph in the history of cryptozoology. It took sixty years to discover it was a toy submarine with some putty on top.</p>
        <p>A hoaxer's revenge. A nation's obsession. And a mystery that <strong>refuses to die</strong>.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- BENTO GRID STATS -->
    <section class="bento-section">
      <div class="bento-grid">

        <div class="bento-card large-card discovery-card">
          <div class="card-content">
            <span class="card-label">The Loch</span>
            <h3 class="card-value">755 ft</h3>
            <p class="card-desc">Maximum depth of Loch Ness — the second-deepest loch in Scotland. Its 7.5 cubic kilometres of peat-dark water hold more fresh water than all the lakes in England and Wales combined.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bento-card check-card">
          <div class="card-content">
            <span class="card-label">Sightings</span>
            <h3 class="card-value text-accent">1,160+</h3>
            <p class="card-desc">Logged in the Official Sightings Register since 1996.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bento-card papers-card">
          <div class="card-content">
            <span class="card-label">The Photo</span>
            <h3 class="card-value">12"</h3>
            <p class="card-desc">Total height of the "monster" in the Surgeon's Photograph. A toy submarine from Woolworth's.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bento-card fraud-card">
          <div class="card-content">
            <span class="card-label">Tourism</span>
            <h3 class="card-value">£41M</h3>
            <p class="card-desc">Annual contribution to the Scottish economy. Half a million visitors per year.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FORENSIC EVIDENCE -->
    <section class="evidence-section">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-label">Exhibit A</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">The Evidence</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="evidence-grid">
        <!-- Item 1 -->
        <div class="evidence-card">
          <div class="evidence-visual">
            <img src={images.surgeons} alt="The Surgeon's Photograph, 1934" />
            <div class="visual-overlay">
              <span class="overlay-label">THE SURGEON'S PHOTOGRAPH: 1934</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="evidence-data">
            <h3>The Hoax</h3>
            <p>The most famous image of the Loch Ness Monster was orchestrated by Marmaduke Wetherell as revenge against the <em>Daily Mail</em>. His stepson-in-law Christian Spurling built a model from a toy submarine and plastic wood. Dr. Robert Kenneth Wilson was recruited as a respectable front man. The hoax was not exposed until Spurling's deathbed confession in 1993.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Item 2 -->
        <div class="evidence-card">
          <div class="evidence-visual">
            <img src={images.plesiosaur} alt="Duria Antiquior — plesiosaurs in their prehistoric habitat" />
            <div class="visual-overlay">
               <span class="overlay-label">THE PLESIOSAUR HYPOTHESIS</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="evidence-data">
            <h3>Ruled Out</h3>
            <p>The romantic idea that a population of plesiosaurs survived in Loch Ness was definitively eliminated by the 2019 eDNA study. No reptilian DNA of any kind was found. The loch is also only 10,000 years old — plesiosaurs went extinct 66 million years ago. A breeding population of air-breathing reptiles in cold, shallow water would be impossible to miss.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Item 3 -->
        <div class="evidence-card">
          <div class="evidence-visual">
            <img src={images.highlands} alt="Morning mist over Loch Ness" />
            <div class="visual-overlay">
               <span class="overlay-label">eDNA STUDY: 2019</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="evidence-data">
            <h3>Giant Eels?</h3>
            <p>Professor Neil Gemmell's team collected 250 water samples and found no DNA from plesiosaurs, sharks, catfish, or sturgeon. But they found European eel DNA at every sampling location in remarkable abundance. "We can't discount the possibility that there may be giant eels in Loch Ness," Gemmell concluded — the most scientifically plausible explanation for sightings.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- TIMELINE -->
    <section class="timeline-section">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-label">Chronology</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">The Hunt</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="timeline">
        <div class="timeline-line"></div>

        <div class="timeline-entry left">
          <span class="timeline-year">1933</span>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <h4>The Road Opens</h4>
            <p>The A82 road along the northern shore is completed, giving motorists the first clear views of Loch Ness. Within months, sightings explode. The <em>Inverness Courier</em> uses the word "monster" for the first time.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="timeline-entry right">
          <span class="timeline-year">APR 1934</span>
          <div class="timeline-content highlight">
            <h4>The Surgeon's Photo</h4>
            <p>The <em>Daily Mail</em> publishes the most famous image of the monster — a long-necked silhouette in calm water. Attributed to Dr. Robert Kenneth Wilson, it defines "Nessie" for sixty years.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="timeline-entry left">
          <span class="timeline-year">1960</span>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <h4>Dinsdale's Film</h4>
            <p>Aeronautical engineer Tim Dinsdale films a moving object on the loch. RAF analysts at JARIC judge it "probably animate." He devotes his remaining life to the search.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="timeline-entry right">
          <span class="timeline-year">OCT 1987</span>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <h4>Operation Deepscan</h4>
            <p>24 boats sweep the entire loch with sonar. Three anomalous contacts are detected but remain unexplained. No conclusive evidence of a large creature is found.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="timeline-entry left">
          <span class="timeline-year">1994</span>
          <div class="timeline-content highlight">
            <h4>The Confession</h4>
            <p>Christian Spurling's deathbed confession reveals the Surgeon's Photograph was a hoax — a toy submarine with a sculpted head, orchestrated by Marmaduke Wetherell as revenge against the <em>Daily Mail</em>.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- KEY FIGURES -->
    <section class="figures-section">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-label">Dossier</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">Key Figures</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="figures-grid">
        <div class="figure-card">
          <div class="figure-image">
            <img src={images.kelpie} alt="The water horse — symbol of Scottish folklore" />
          </div>
          <div class="figure-info">
            <span class="figure-role">The Hoaxer</span>
            <h3>Marmaduke Wetherell</h3>
            <p>Big-game hunter hired by the <em>Daily Mail</em> in 1933. After his hippopotamus-foot tracks were exposed, he orchestrated the Surgeon's Photograph as revenge — recruiting his son, stepson-in-law, and a London surgeon to create the most enduring hoax in cryptozoological history.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="figure-card">
          <div class="figure-image">
            <img src={images.columba} alt="Saint Columba confronts the water beast" />
          </div>
          <div class="figure-info">
            <span class="figure-role">The First Witness</span>
            <h3>Saint Columba</h3>
            <p>Irish abbot whose encounter with a "water beast" in the River Ness circa 565 AD is the earliest written account of a creature in these waters. The story, recorded by his biographer Adomnan, was a miracle narrative — proof of the saint's holy power, not a naturalist's observation.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CONCLUSION -->
    <section class="conclusion-section">
      <div class="conclusion-grid">
        <div class="conclusion-image">
          <img src={images.urquhartRuins} alt="Urquhart Castle ruins above Loch Ness" />
          <div class="image-caption">Urquhart Castle above Loch Ness. The most common location for sightings.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="conclusion-text">
          <h2>The Monster That Won't Die</h2>
          <p>The photograph was a toy submarine. The flipper was painted. The gargoyle head was a tree stump. The DNA says eels.</p>
          <p>And still, every year, half a million people come to Loch Ness and look out across the water. <em>The monster is not in the loch. It's in the looking.</em></p>

          <div class="cta-box" id="ctaBox">
            <h3 id="ctaTitle">Get the Full Book</h3>
            <p>The complete story of the hoaxers, the believers, the scientists, and the myth that refuses to die.</p>
            <button onclick={`localStorage.setItem('historiqly_purchasing','loch-ness-monster');window.location.href='${stripeUrl}'`} class="btn-buy-primary cta-buy" id="ctaBuyBtn">
              <span class="btn-buy-text">Buy the Book</span>
              <span class="btn-buy-price">$2.99</span>
            </button>
            <a href="/books/epub/loch-ness-monster.epub" class="btn-download-primary cta-download" id="ctaDownloadBtn" style="display:none;" download>
              <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5">
                <path d="M21 15v4a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2v-4"></path>
                <polyline points="7 10 12 15 17 10"></polyline>
                <line x1="12" y1="15" x2="12" y2="3"></line>
              </svg>
              Download Your Book
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </article>
</SidebarLayout>

<script>
  // Purchase detection (fallback — homepage handles the main redirect)
  const params = new URLSearchParams(window.location.search);
  if (params.get('purchased') === 'true') {
    localStorage.setItem('historiqly_purchased_loch-ness-monster', 'true');
    localStorage.removeItem('historiqly_purchasing');
    history.replaceState({}, '', window.location.pathname);
  }

  const hasPurchased = localStorage.getItem('historiqly_purchased_loch-ness-monster') === 'true';

  if (hasPurchased) {
    // Hero buttons
    const heroBuy = document.getElementById('heroBuyBtn');
    const heroDownload = document.getElementById('heroDownloadBtn');
    if (heroBuy) heroBuy.style.display = 'none';
    if (heroDownload) heroDownload.style.display = 'inline-flex';

    // CTA buttons
    const ctaBuy = document.getElementById('ctaBuyBtn');
    const ctaDownload = document.getElementById('ctaDownloadBtn');
    const ctaTitle = document.getElementById('ctaTitle');
    if (ctaBuy) ctaBuy.style.display = 'none';
    if (ctaDownload) ctaDownload.style.display = 'inline-flex';
    if (ctaTitle) ctaTitle.textContent = 'Your Book Is Ready';
  }
</script>

<style>
  /* SWISS TECHNICAL BENTO THEME */
  :root {
    --bg-dark: #0a0a0a;
    --bg-card: #111111;
    --bg-card-hover: #161616;
    --border-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
    --text-primary: #FAFAFA;
    --text-secondary: #A1A1AA;
    --accent: #F59E0B;
    --accent-dim: rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.1);

    --font-serif: 'Cormorant Garamond', Georgia, serif;
    --font-sans: 'Inter', system-ui, sans-serif;
  }

  .case-file {
    background-color: var(--bg-dark);
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    overflow-x: hidden;
  }

  /* UTILS */
  .text-accent { color: var(--accent); }

  /* HERO */
  .hero {
    position: relative;
    height: 90vh;
    min-height: 600px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
  }

  .hero-bg {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    z-index: 0;
  }

  .hero-bg img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
    filter: brightness(0.4) grayscale(0.8) contrast(1.2);
  }

  .hero-overlay {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: radial-gradient(circle at center, transparent 0%, var(--bg-dark) 90%);
  }

  .hero-content {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 10;
    text-align: center;
    max-width: 900px;
    padding: 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .case-meta {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    justify-content: center;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .meta-badge {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 0.4rem 0.8rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.5);
    backdrop-filter: blur(4px);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  .meta-badge.alert {
    border-color: var(--accent);
    color: var(--accent);
    background: var(--accent-dim);
  }

  .meta-badge.price {
    border-color: var(--accent);
    background: var(--accent-dim);
    color: var(--accent);
    font-weight: 800;
  }

  .hero-title {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: clamp(3.5rem, 8vw, 6rem);
    line-height: 0.9;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    text-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(0,0,0,0.7);
  }

  .hero-subtitle {
    font-size: clamp(1.1rem, 3vw, 1.5rem);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-weight: 300;
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }

  .hero-stats {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 3rem;
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1);
  }

  .stat {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .stat-label {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .stat-value {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .scroll-indicator {
    position: absolute;
    bottom: 2rem;
    left: 50%;
    transform: translateX(-50%);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1rem;
    z-index: 10;
  }

  .scroll-indicator span {
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.3em;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    opacity: 0.7;
  }

  .scroll-line {
    width: 1px;
    height: 60px;
    background: linear-gradient(to bottom, var(--text-secondary) 0%, transparent 100%);
  }

  /* HERO ACTIONS */
  .hero-actions {
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }

  .btn-buy-primary {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1rem;
    padding: 1rem 2.5rem;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #F59E0B 0%, #D97706 100%);
    color: #000;
    border: none;
    border-radius: 8px;
    cursor: pointer;
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    transition: all 0.25s;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 24px rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.3), 0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
  }

  .btn-buy-primary:hover {
    transform: translateY(-3px);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 32px rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.45), 0 4px 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #FBBF24 0%, #F59E0B 100%);
  }

  .btn-buy-text {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  }

  .btn-buy-price {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem;
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15);
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  .btn-download-primary {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    padding: 1rem 2.5rem;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #5DB585 0%, #4a9e70 100%);
    color: #000;
    text-decoration: none;
    border: none;
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    transition: all 0.25s;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 24px rgba(93, 181, 133, 0.3), 0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
  }

  .btn-download-primary:hover {
    transform: translateY(-3px);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 32px rgba(93, 181, 133, 0.45), 0 4px 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #6FC494 0%, #5DB585 100%);
  }

  .cta-buy, .cta-download {
    width: 100%;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  /* INTRO */
  .intro-section {
    padding: 8rem 1.5rem;
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .intro-text p {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 3vw, 1.75rem);
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .intro-text strong {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  /* BENTO GRID */
  .bento-section {
    padding: 2rem 1.5rem 8rem;
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .bento-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(1, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .bento-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
      grid-template-rows: repeat(2, minmax(200px, auto));
    }

    .large-card {
      grid-column: span 2;
      grid-row: span 2;
    }
  }

  .bento-card {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    transition: transform 0.3s ease, border-color 0.3s ease;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  .bento-card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    border-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.2);
    background: var(--bg-card-hover);
  }

  .card-label {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .card-value {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 3rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .discovery-card .card-value { font-size: 5rem; font-weight: 700; }
  .check-card .card-value { font-size: 4rem; }

  .card-desc {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  /* EVIDENCE */
  .evidence-section {
    padding: 4rem 1.5rem;
    background: #0F0F0F;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
  }

  .section-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .section-label {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .section-title {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 3rem;
    font-weight: 400;
  }

  .evidence-grid {
    max-width: 1000px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    display: grid;
    gap: 4rem;
  }

  .evidence-card {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 2rem;
    align-items: center;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .evidence-card {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    }
    .evidence-card:nth-child(even) .evidence-visual {
      order: 2;
    }
  }

  .evidence-visual {
    position: relative;
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
  }

  .evidence-visual img {
    width: 100%;
    display: block;
    filter: brightness(0.8) contrast(1.1);
  }

  .visual-overlay {
    position: absolute;
    bottom: 0;
    left: 0;
